definition: to duplicate/to make a copy of/to copy/to reproduce/to clone

sentences.english: This records the start and end time of the reproduction.

sentences.english: Scenes from the 17th century landscape paintings were replicated as Arcadian scenes.

sentences.english: He also created a functioning replica of MySpace's log-in page.
sentences.chinese: 斯克姆還創建了MySpace的登陸網頁的複製品。

sentences.english: Transcriptionally active regions are replicated first.
Items are copied starting at the specified index of the target array.

sentences.english: Q13. What if someone copies my Registered Design?
sentences.chinese: 如果有人複製我已註冊的外觀設計該怎麼辦？

sentences.english: "Salmonella doubles every 20 minutes under ideal conditions," Keener said.
sentences.chinese: 基納說，在理想環境下，沙門氏菌每20分鐘複製。

sentences.english: Select the address string and copy it to the clipboard.

sentences.english: Do you know that scientists a sheep into an .

sentences.english: Pastes previously copied or cut clipboard contents.
sentences.chinese: 粘貼先前複製或剪切的剪貼板內容。

sentences.english: Select all six frames and duplicate.

sentences.english: Create and copy virtual machine images to multiple workstations.
sentences.chinese: 創建並複製虛擬機映像到多個工作站。

sentences.english: It applies an XSLT style sheet as it copies the file to the target directory.

sentences.english: The non-transactions sites are trying to replicate the unique product set without the costs.

sentences.english: Discover COM: Connection Points Versus M - This module is designed to solve the old problem of directory replication.
